caption: Love the spicy garlic ramen
Service was amazing. Highly recommend!

So so so good! Thank you Gabby for your amazing service. Everyone here was super nice and the karaage *sp?* ramen was a perfect little warm up before heading home. Thank you for being so nice Gabby! Cant wait to come back!
Said close at 9pm when hours show 1030pm close. Plus when we got there the door was open and there was someone eating at the counter at 9:51pm. Laziness and lack of customer service. What a shame.

Very bad experience. Servers in the restaurant have very bad attitude. Also they will never let you know when the table is going to be ready. Even for ordering online, I asked that how long is the wait, they told me 15mins but I waited over 40 mins. That’s ridiculous. No reason to come in again. The first time I order, there was no one in the store. They told me it will take less than 5 mins to be ready but I still waited for 15 mins.

Not sure if ownership changed or something but this place got so much better since the last time I came! Their udon is super flavorful and the noodles are great, arguably a little soft but I like them that way. They have really good tempura, tho I wish they'd add onion. This is my new fave udon spot!
One of my preferred places for delicious ramen. The service was very welcoming and sociable.
Ramen and the feeling at this location is excellent. Really nothing but great experiences here, so I will be back. They have a lot of good reviews for a reason.
Ramen and the setting here is very good. Filled me up in no time. Certainly worth going back to. Prices that won't break you.
Open. Back. Up. I miss your ramen :(
Tastes great nonetheless! Sesame ice cream wasn’t as good as I remembered it to be. Felt there was too much ice within. Perhaps defrosted and Re frozen. Char siew for the win!
Are you guys ever going to reopen?
This place is great and spacious, the meals was yummy and the rates were very fair. fast, productive service and very attentive staff members. Highly recommended.
Love this place! Chill ambiance, delicious food, friendly staff, and they always know how to make my ramen meal enjoyable. Keep doing what you’re doing :)
I love this place! Delicious broth with noodles.

Went here for weekday lunch. Light crowd pre-noon. Very excellent service and I like how they brought over the Canadian practice of running your credit card from a device right at your table. The original ramen, which uses a tonkotsu broth, was creamy rich and delicious. Thick noodles were a good compliment. They go light on the toppings, which you mostly have to add on extra and can get pricey from a $12 base. But no complaints since the noodle and broth themselves were so good. Added gyoza and a Coke for another $4. Not cheap overall but also not too unusual for a good Chicago place. Probably one of the best ramen places in Chicago downtown area! $2 sapporo drafts and 1/2 off apps for happy hour - might go back for that!

I had such an amazing time here at the establishment the people are more than welcoming and helpful the food is to die for the servings are huge this is a awesome awesome place the atmosphere is beautiful the green line train is very close Shout out to Paul Lee for an outstanding experience I am a forever customer now
Spicy bowl of Japanese style noodles that hits the stomach on a cold wintry day.
Not the best ramen but def decent.  Very nice staff.
excellent!
Great food and love the happy hour deals best place/atmosphere. I love how you get to watch your food prepared as well. Customer service was awesome

(Translated by Google) Fast serving and serving good food, especially on cold Chicago days and evenings.  (Original) Бързо обслужване и сервиране на добра храна, подходяща особено в студените чикагски дни и вечери.

This restaurant is my preferable site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this place. Whenever  I feel like having a superb meal, this is the place that comes right away to my mind. good and all kinds of  food and a large menu.generous staff, and good ambience. In addition to that, the tariff is good. I sent my friends to this spot with no hesitation.
Just what this city needs, another inexperienced group of people preparing ramen.
Great food, friendly personnel 😁👍
Always solid food and service

白胡麻坦々麺 (Shirogoma Tantanmen) Rich but not to rich that you get tired of it. The grounded pork centered on top seasoned deliciously and flavorful. As you start eating the ramen, just when you think it could not get any better, the pork starts mixing in and changes the profile of the broth. Probably one of the most authentic ramen shops that I have come across not just the flavor, but the greetings as well いらっしゃいませ、ありがとうございます。
Great food!! the service and comfort of the restaurant was a little lacking and the prices were kinda high

Came in for lunch with some coworkers. Quite an impressive selection of different varieties of pork and chicken ramen.  The gyoza were nice and crispy.  I went with the Chicken Karaage Miso Ramen with thick noodles. It was 🔥 delicious. Highly recommend.

Really good soup with chicken and pork options, a variety of intensities/spiciness, and the chance to add your favorite toppings.  A broad selection of appetizers, too - the gyoza are a definite enhancement compared to typical fare.  I like this place a lot .
The ramen was delicious and staff are super friendly. I got their seasonal spicy ramen and it was SPICY! Definitely did not disappoint. Would definitely go again.
Diggin’ their ramen! I got the garlic pork! And the Hot Karaage is awesome! The best was realizing we went during happy hour !
Pretty good overall. We experienced slow service. Somewhat pricey. I ordered the chicken jalapeño ramen with an egg which was great but I suggest getting the pork spicy garlic with Jalepeno.
Some of the best ramen I've had in Chicago for the price - it's build your own bowl, and the vegan options are so good!

Their Ramen is so good- We ordered their ramen through DoorDash (great prices too) and got the spicy pork with gluten-free noodles, and the pork miso with thick ramen noodles and I would most definitely order again. Highly recommend.
Great service, great food, never disappointed
Love the atmosphere and people here! Great ramen broth and noodles. Can be a little pricey, but there are great happy hour specials!
Excellent and friendly staff. Take your time to decide what items you want in your bowl... we plan to return to try more of them. Dessert was great. Restrooms are really nice too!

We went to Kinton ramen on a Friday evening - the new location in West Loop. This was definitely worth the stop (though it’s on a not-so-busy street). The ambience of the place is pretty good and the music is great if you like hip hop. The ramen itself it’s pretty tasty. I got spicy garlic pork ramen. The flavors were pretty well blended and the thick noodles were fresh.  I will say that they could work on the quality of the cuts of meet that are included in the ramen bowl. It seems also like an after thought.  I had a Sapporo beef which was $2 for happy hour that was fresh and crisp.  I will definitely come back here for ramen; a top three spot for sure. And I would recommend it as a good first ever spot to try if you have never had ramen. Cheers!

I'm often disappointed with ramen places, but Kinton Ramen is definitely one that I'd be happy to go back anytime.  It is popular and busy but service was still friendly and the portion was generous for price.  I had the Pork Original soup with thick noodles and it's a good benchmark ramen.  Try the Yuzu Lemonade!
This is my absolute favorite ramen place in the city. Go to order is the Original Pork with bamboo shoots and garlic oil. Be sure to also grab a Yuzu Lemonade!
The have a black ramen special during Hawks/Bulls home games that is 👌.
My husband and I loved it! Will be coming back soon!
One of my favorite ramen places in Chicago! Friendly staff 💪
Good ramen and good service! They have happy hours too from Monday through Friday.

We came in and sat down at a table, nobody showed us to our table. We sat for 25 minutes waiting for someone to even be friendly, nobody waited on us or even said hello. We were completely ignored. A ramen shop has fast and friendly service but this one did not. I’ve seen ramen shops 3 times as busy as this one pull off a well executed restaurant. Absolutely ridiculous!!!
Great service, hoping to return soon. I'm not a ramen expert but it was pretty good. Price is affordable which is really nice, the decor and atmosphere is great also.
Pork spicy garlic ramen was very tasty. Nice amount of heat without setting your mouth on fire.
Very good food, staff and chefs very alert and engage with customers. The atmosphere is very relaxing. Will be going back.
This place might be my new favorite ramen spot. Spicy pork ramen was simple, yet super flavorful. Good happy hour and good service.
I don’t know why but in the Miso Ramen there is no corn. Meanwhile, more intolerable is that they add Garlic Oil in the Miso. Absolutely not real Japanese style of Ramen. Not recommended.

Very tasty ramen with authentic and flavourful soup base with a wide range of different options available. Noodles themselves were also nice - chewy with a good bite. The manager and staff were very friendly and welcoming. Would highly recommend a visit to this establishment or any of their other branches. Very satisfying experience!

Best👏 ramen👏 around👏 The dish got served looked like the photo on the menu (where do you see that these days?) and tastes amazing. The broth is perfect, I would recommend the thick noodles option for any ramen dish you order (Shoutout to Victoria, one of the hosts for recommending that option).  The prices aren't high, but the quality is. ¯_(ツ)_/¯
Nice food. Love the broths.
Best ramen I've had in Chicago so far!
Good ramen, not expensive. The service was not the best, they seem to be working out the kinks still.
Ramen was good. Water in silver cups makes it hard for wait staff to see if you need more water. Even worse is when you ask for water 4 times, then have to get your own pitcher of water.

(Translated by Google) Very general! The pork in the Miso pork is not only a very unsweet taste. The four kinds of snacks are also ordinary and unrelenting. In short, it is not worth running for a try!  (Original) 很一般！点的Miso pork 里面的猪肉不仅柴还有一种很不新鲜的味道。点的四种小吃也是普普通通无功无过。总之不值得特地跑来一试！
It was good but they have me my bill halfway through my meal before I was even done. I was alone and felt like they were kicking me out.
Very good ramen with attention to detail. Excellent staff
Excellent vibes and very amiable service. The food was fresh and yummy. Will definitely recommend this spot to friends and family. Reasonable rates and large portions. Keep up the great work.

Comparable to Ramen San, the ramen wasn't all that spectacular. However, a noticable difference from Kinton's broth and the competitions is how light it settled on the pallet. The sodium and pork levels were very muted, but complimented each other in a unique way.
Food is okay, but quantity is small. Unfair to compare to Ramen in Japan, but a 7 to 8 for USA standard of ramen.

Delicious ramen! The meat is very tender and juicy, the ramen chewy, and the soup very flavorful without being salty. The fried chicken was surprising being buffalo chicken flavored, not Japanese spicy. The service was pleasant and quick. Metered or free street parking, credit accepted

Very friendly and professional service. My boyfriend really enjoyed their ramen and he is a picky person who has tried almost all ramen restaurants in Chicago. So his "approval " is credible haha. I really like their appetizers, especially the gyoza (must try). The fried chicken is really crispy if you have the original version. Their happy hour of half off appetizers are only Monday to Friday 4-7pm. I would go there again.
Got the salmon and the veggie ramen because I didnt want pork broth and didnt have a taste for chicken. I left satisfied and will be going back again. Oh and the staff was great too.
Very rich broth. Spicy pork ramen really spicy!

Ramen is fine. But they charge for 12.98 tip without asking? The waitress kept asking us “should I bring the check?” That’s really annoying. I mean, there is still available spot and there was no queue waiting. We were not finished with our food. Why so rush to ask us to pay and then charge me 12.98 tip without asking? The food is only 57.85 and she charged me 12.98 for tip??? Will not come again, the tip is just too scary.
Food is good, service is bad.
If I had the money and fit body, I would digest this Roman daily. Flavor is magnificent, staff are welcoming and beautiful and the set up is clean. I WILL be back.
I’m giving it 3 stars due to the ambiance and excellent customer service. I wasn’t a fan of the ramen. The ramen didn’t have much flavor and was very bland.
For decent ramen in Chicago, this may be a better place than most
Favorite Ramen in Chicago! Thick and flavorful broth, with great topping options. The space has a good ambiance with a unique experience.
Great food. Amazing happy hour specials!
We were disappointed that they charged us extra for green iced tea refills when it wasn't communicated up front. Pork in the ramen was very fatty.

I gave it 2 stars just for the ambiance. The ramen is very bland none of the “seasoned vegetables” were seasoned, they were anything but. I ordered the vegetarian ramen with thick noodles and the fried broccoli (which was good), but the ramen left little to be desired. Highly disappointed $22 later. It was like the vegetables were not even cooked. I am holding the cabbage. Try your luck. Others seem to love it. I will not be a returning customer.
Great place for happy hour. 2$ beers and half off apps. What more could someone want
Good ramen but could rone down the salt. I've been twice and a bit too salty both times
Solid ramen and fairly priced
the food is delicious, atmosphere is great, wonderful staff, great location. must try the black sesame seed mochi icecream

We visited Kinton for ramen and while the sides were delicious the miso base of the ramen we got was a bit flat lacking richness. It's a cozy place with very friendly service and it totally worths the try!

This restaurant was in my suggestion best new place to visit for ramen in Chicago but since it was not near my place I couldn’t go before. Driving downtown and after finishing some errand we decided to drive to the west loop since it's nearby and try-finally this restaurant.  When we walked it was actually empty, that was ok for us because we're hungry. First impressions were actually wow this place looks beautiful and very trendy, I'm sure prices will be high since it's new and it was in the heart of the west loop. My hubby and I looked at the menu and prices were actually affordable, $11 for ramen can't beat that.  I got the normal Miso ramen 🍜 and hubby the spicy garlic one. For 4 dollars more you could upgrade the plate to add an appetizer, we got small spicy chicken ( karaage chicken)  and also fry octopus balls (takoyaki). While waiting for the food we got first the appetizers which they were delicious and then at 4 pm the happy hour starts so we got both $2 dollars Sapporo beers super cold, the way should be. Finally, our Ramen bowls arrived and wow they were actually great and very good portion. In the beginning, I saw the size of the bowl and I thought it was too small but we actually couldn’t even finish, we were so full. I generally don't give 5 stars to a restaurant because there’s always room for improvement but this one earned it, we had such a great time there and our server was such a sweetheart, I wish I could remember her name to also add it on this review. Now that winter it’s almost here, this is the place to visit for some amazing Japanese food, highly recommended.

Was caught off guard and delighted to see the first kinton chain open in the US. The broth is thick and filling, the noodles soak in the flavour, the pork belly is torched and caramelized. Such a good bowl of ramen.😋
Very clean and efficient restaurant.  Food was very good, hot and fast! Prices are reasonable. Nice gem of a restaurant in a sea of food choices! Definitely Recommended !

Ramen fanatic here...this ramen really nailed it. Love the flavor! Prices are really incredible, and the starters are so great and also priced well. Happy hour drinks prices are great. I will have to come back for it.  Broth was perfect, noodles were cooked to perfection, and the toppings were perfect too. The matcha cheesecake is also super good!  Love the space, vibes are very good. Service is quick and not so fussy. Can’t wait to come back and try the seasonal amazements. I loved my server, I hope to see her again on my next visit.  The only ramen place in chicago that I have tried and have been satisfied with.

First ramen place in Chicago that offers cheese as a side!!! So happy and satisfied! Please try it if you haven't yet. It's great that they setup the menu with so many option to customize everything, but if you add everything other ramen pieces normally included, this ramen would be a lot more expensive. Nevertheless, it was pretty good in everything. I wouldn't say it was outstanding but it was not bad at all. This place can beat many nearby ramen places without the long wait.
Delicious ramen, some exotic, delicious dishes

The way my friend described this ramen place was that they offer a minimal ramen experience and if you want the full one you would have to pay extra. I think I find that true with the dressings on the ramen tend to be quite minimal. You have to pay for nori, you have to pay for an egg, you have to pay for anything that isn't listed on the description and I think that took me by surprise. I don't know how we can take a simple Japanese thing like ramen in charge almost $20 per bowl.
Amazing ramen it is. Thick, bouncy noodle with flavorful broth, AND FRY CHICKENS ON TOP!!! Apps and drinks are okay, come at happy hour and the price is decent.
Delicious!!
The flavor is good but I got stomachs in the whole afternoon (went to restroom three times) wondering if the food is safe or not. Afraid to go there again...
Super delicious ramen. Excellent service. Would recommend if you find yourself craving ramen in the West loop
Great wasabi
Such a great vibe as soon as you walk in the door! Ramen was delicious!
I lived in westloop and tried every Ramen restaurant. This is my new favorite. Flavorful broth but not salty. Reasonably price and good combo options. Love the service too. Lisa was wonderful.
One of my new favorite ramen places in Chicago! Their karaage ramen is amazing!

(Translated by Google) Beautiful ramen shop in Fulton. The interior is modern but the amount of ramen or broth is not at all decent. The amount is so small that the male man lacks ramen. It is a restaurant where people who have not eaten ramen in the East can keep coming.  (Original) 풀턴에 있는 인테리어가 이쁜 라멘집. 인테리어는 모던하지만 라멘의 양이나 국물은 전혀 먹을만하지 않다. 양도 매우 작아서 성인 남성 가준으로는 라멘하나로 부족하다. 동양에서 라멘을 못 먹어본 사람들이 계속 올 수 있는 식당이다.
Delicious! Heads and shoulders above Furious Spoon. The broth here is amazing. You've gotta try it!
Get the chilled tsukemen! You get some noodles, dip it in the broth, and profit!
original broth is legit
Very nice and polite staff, great service. Food is perfect! The hot karaage is wonderful. And the noodles? Great!

If you are vegetarian, I would recommend to not go -- the vegetarian ramen broth has no flavor and the noodles are of instant ramen quality.  Seems like they prioritize ramen with meats.  Otherwise, the staff is very friendly and offers promos
Good food
Best ramen in the city

Their spicy soup is awesome. Love the flavor and the kick it has. Pretty nice ambience. All the waiters greet everyone as they walk in and out of the restaurant. This can get pretty annoying after being there for a while. Other than that the food is great.
Pretty good spot. The apps were very good, ramen was good but not great. Staff was incredibly friendly.
Delicious
Excellent food, great service. I spent ten years in Japan and I went with a Japanese friend, and we both loved it.

We were very excited to find out that Kinton Ramen opened a branch in Chicago.Finally a good ramen place to eat here. I tried the pork miso ramen and it was very good. Best ramen in Chicago by far! Broth was flavorful and the noodles were chewy. We had takoyaki for appetizers. My only issue was that it did not have that much octopus in it.But nonetheless good. So happy we finally have a good ramen place to eat in here. Staff were also very attentive and nice.Please open more branches in the south suburbs so we don’t have to travel far to dine in.
4.5 star food, 5 star service.
Great  ramen. Apps were very tasty. Service was on point.

Professional workers , cool atmosphere but the ramen lacked flavor in my opinion. my wife on the other hand loved it. The broth was light and the noodles was too chewy,  we ordered the shoyu ramen which is soy sauce based and I hardly tasted the soy sauce.  The salmen appetizer was too small for 9 bucks  overall cool experience I could see myself coming back in the future considering they just opened up they could always improve.
Great food, fun atmosphere.
Staff very nice . Cute place, dumpling appetizer wonderful.  The ramen ..... disappointing. Sorry

New ramen place in west loop! This place has a great decor, and the service is good. Now let's talk about the food. Pork ramen: on par with expectation, but lacks a bit of depth in flavor. You will need to add toppings to it. Takoyaki was tasty, but was not a big fan of the karage. Overall, I think there are some improvements that could boost this place. Will return in the future to check back again.

I got the pork miso, it was very creamy. The only thing I think it lacked was having not having vegetables, all it had was green onion which is delicious but you have to pay extra for veggies... Other than that it was very good.
Very tasty ramen! Awesome service!
they have ramen here
Just opened last month. This is a Canadian ramen chain. The both is very good and the flavor is just right.  Pro Tip: Make sure you finish the whole bowl, including the soup to get a stamp card.

This is a place with unfulfilled potential. The ramen egg was overcooked. The broth I had lack depth. (The original was good though)  Pros: No lines Cons: Overcooked ramen egg, the server apologized and said that they will remove the egg from the check and didn't hold true to their words.

The service was great, and karaage pretty good (nice and crispy). I felt that the ramen lacked flavor, boldness, and depth. The broth was  really watered down (I had Pork Original). The apps I think are the better route to take.

New ramen shop in the west loop. Tried the spicy pork bowl and gyoza. The gyoza was cooked well, crispy edges and a little more chew to the center. I don't understand aioli sauce, traditional soy with some vinegar would work well or some chili oil. Bowl with egg was fine, decent heat while still being able to taste it. Service was a bit overbearing, assuming it's because they just opened.
Soup was ok...I got the chicken shyo had a weird taste and the workers legit scream at you in Chinese when u walk in and out it’s scary
This is my new favorite ramen place. The pork spicy garlic ramen (with egg) was delicious! I also tried their hot karage and chiki chiki don -- excellent. Highly recommend!
This place rocks!
Delicious ramen with a great selection. Friendly staff too to walk you through the options. Good lunch special! Includes ramen, gyoza and edamame for $14.

I ordered the miso pork ramen with butter, corn, bamboo shoots. I had a side of takoyaki and a yuzu lemonade. I really enjoyed the yuzu lemonade it was  quite sour but I love sour. The takoyaki was fresh and solid 8/10. The miso pork was good I would have like a spicy option but overall was a nice light broth. Service was good and everyone is nice.

Wow these folks LOVE me. ngl it’s probably because I’m a huge influencer 💆🏻‍♂️ kinda felt like that scene in tampopo where they insult the ramen shop & then she dreams that they’re coming to beat her up 😆 nice bowl nice broth 🐖 👄
